                     <p>The objective of this part of the study was to use the tools of ideal type, a “portrait,” to provide the background to examine both the ways in which conflicts of values are lived and the ways in which ethical decisions are made in long-term care units of pediatric hospitals. The most fruitful result of this documentary research has come as<italic>insights</italic>into the professional interaction of physicians, nurses and social workers. This interaction is considered on both intraprofessional and interprofessional levels.</p>
